Broker-Dealer Stakeholder
A Broker-Dealer is a brokerage firm with a licence to as a market maker for securities. In other words, is allowed to keep risky financial positions in its own balance sheet awaiting to transact with its customers. The difference between a market maker and a broker dealer is that a broker dealer is not obliged to give its customers two-way prices.

A Broker-Dealer is a brokerage firm with a licence to as a market maker for securities. In other words, is allowed to keep risky financial positions in its own balance sheet awaiting to transact with its customers. The difference between a market maker and a broker dealer is that a broker dealer is not obliged to give its customers two-way prices.
